1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:03,970
(To bake his childhood dream into bread,)

2
00:00:02,340 --> 00:00:04,070
This cream bread...

3
00:00:04,310 --> 00:00:08,110
is not the cream bread that I've made and sold at my store.

4
00:00:04,610 --> 00:00:08,080
(instead of making his shop's popular signature bread,)

5
00:00:08,280 --> 00:00:10,979
There's bread I've always wanted to make in the past.

6
00:00:08,850 --> 00:00:11,680
(Lim Hoon baked the cream bread he really wanted to make.)

7
00:00:10,980 --> 00:00:12,280
I wanted to prove that.

8
00:00:12,850 --> 00:00:15,350
(I want to say farewell to my cream bread.)

9
00:00:16,120 --> 00:00:18,359
So this is the bread that captures your life,

10
00:00:18,360 --> 00:00:19,490
but you elevated it.

11
00:00:19,720 --> 00:00:20,960
Yes, that's right.

12
00:00:21,890 --> 00:00:24,060
Now we will see whether The Yeonnam-dong Hit Cream Bread,

13
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:27,600
Contender Lim Hoon passed or failed.

14
00:00:30,230 --> 00:00:32,839
(Lim Hoon's cream bread filled with his joys and sorrows)

15
00:00:30,330 --> 00:00:32,540
Is it a pass or a fail?

16
00:00:32,840 --> 00:00:35,610
(What's the result of the bread that embodies his life?)

17
00:00:32,970 --> 00:00:34,510
Please show us the result.

18
00:00:36,310 --> 00:00:39,009
I've been making just cream bread for 12 years.

19
00:00:39,010 --> 00:00:41,610
Today, I'd like to see what I got out of all those years.

20
00:00:42,750 --> 00:00:46,120
(The Yeonnam-dong Hit Cream Bread, Lim Hoon)

21
00:00:47,520 --> 00:00:49,050
(No way.)

22
00:00:48,990 --> 00:00:52,290
Oh, no. I thought he'd get a pass without any problems.

23
00:00:53,390 --> 00:00:55,660
(Lim Hoon's cream bread goes past the Pass Zone.)

24
00:00:55,630 --> 00:00:57,930
Contender Lim Hoon, you have failed.

25
00:00:57,060 --> 00:00:59,059
(He challenged himself with a new cream bread,)

26
00:00:59,060 --> 00:01:01,060
(but he failed in the end.)

27
00:01:03,970 --> 00:01:05,970
I knew I'd fail,

28
00:01:06,400 --> 00:01:08,270
but I wanted to bake it this way anyway.

29
00:01:08,910 --> 00:01:10,240
That was what I wanted.

30
00:01:11,340 --> 00:01:12,840
You're a soulmate to your cream bread.

31
00:01:14,650 --> 00:01:16,979
- Well done, today. - Thank you.

32
00:01:14,750 --> 00:01:18,920
(Thank you for showing us the cream bread of your dream.)

33
00:01:16,980 --> 00:01:19,280
- You did great. - Thank you.

34
00:01:22,050 --> 00:01:25,820
Though the result was disappointing, it was my choice.

35
00:01:27,390 --> 00:01:28,390
Yes.

36
00:01:29,060 --> 00:01:30,360
I should accept it.

37
00:01:32,860 --> 00:01:36,570
(The contest continues.)

38
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:35,670
What kind of bread will come out next?

39
00:01:42,040 --> 00:01:45,310
(Various signature breads that catch your eye)

40
00:01:49,310 --> 00:01:51,379
What's great about a survival show is...

41
00:01:51,380 --> 00:01:52,880
that there are pastries, breads,

42
00:01:55,090 --> 00:01:58,760
and chocolates. We can see all the techniques there are.

43
00:01:55,250 --> 00:01:57,119
(All kinds of bread, including desserts,)

44
00:01:57,120 --> 00:01:59,020
(have come to Bake Your Dream.)

45
00:02:01,060 --> 00:02:03,190
- Hey, it's a car. - Yes.

46
00:02:03,430 --> 00:02:04,860
It's sugarcraft.

47
00:02:04,130 --> 00:02:06,899
(Sugarcraft: A type of food art that creates ...)

48
00:02:05,660 --> 00:02:07,229
After shaping the cake,

49
00:02:06,900 --> 00:02:10,730
(decorations, sculptures, and cakes using processed sugar.)

50
00:02:07,230 --> 00:02:10,399
you cover it delicately with the dough made of sugar.

51
00:02:10,400 --> 00:02:13,439
- So there's a type of cake... - Right.

52
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:15,770
- that's called sugarcraft? - Yes. It's different.

53
00:02:16,510 --> 00:02:20,080
Hello, I've been running a sugar cake shop for seven years.

54
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:22,910
I'm Kim Seon Yong, the Police Pastry Chef.

55
00:02:20,240 --> 00:02:21,649
(Police Pastry Chef, Kim Seon Yong)

56
00:02:21,650 --> 00:02:23,080
(Sugarcraft Instructor, popular for cakes for celebrity in Gangseo)

57
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:26,650
I've worked as a police officer for seven years.

58
00:02:24,210 --> 00:02:27,050
(Worked as a police officer for 7 years)

59
00:02:27,080 --> 00:02:31,390
I studied the arts from a young age until high school.

60
00:02:31,520 --> 00:02:33,919
I like creating stuff with my hands.

61
00:02:33,920 --> 00:02:36,530
That's why I quit working as a cop and became a pastry chef.

62
00:02:37,930 --> 00:02:40,760
But he has chosen a different car than a police car.

63
00:02:44,030 --> 00:02:45,300
There's chicken stock.

64
00:02:45,570 --> 00:02:46,800
That's right.

65
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:50,310
(That's right)

66
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:51,610
She's singing.

67
00:02:52,110 --> 00:02:54,040
I think she's a music teacher.

68
00:02:54,610 --> 00:02:57,209
- I heard she's the oldest. - Yes. She's supposed to be.

69
00:02:57,210 --> 00:02:58,850
She's 73 years old.

70
00:02:57,980 --> 00:03:00,420
(The oldest contender, at the age of 73)

71
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:03,319
I worked as a music teacher...

72
00:03:03,320 --> 00:03:05,619
at school for a long time.

73
00:03:05,620 --> 00:03:07,159
As part of an after-school class,

74
00:03:06,120 --> 00:03:10,390
(She started baking with students for an after-school class.)

75
00:03:07,160 --> 00:03:09,660
I tried baking with my students.

76
00:03:09,790 --> 00:03:12,829
I bake bread with music.

77
00:03:12,830 --> 00:03:16,200
That's why my nickname is Singing Baker.

78
00:03:15,230 --> 00:03:16,669
(Singing Baker, Cheon Pil Sun)

79
00:03:16,670 --> 00:03:18,500
(Music Teacher's Bakery in Geumsan, 41 years of baking experience)

80
00:03:18,670 --> 00:03:20,639
Are you making campagne?

81
00:03:20,640 --> 00:03:21,969
Yes, with sourdough.

82
00:03:21,970 --> 00:03:24,469
I believe I was the first one to bake ginseng sourdough.

83
00:03:24,470 --> 00:03:25,580
- Really? - Yes.

84
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:28,180
(Ginseng sourdough)

85
00:03:25,710 --> 00:03:27,339
- I'll look forward to it. - Okay. Thanks.

86
00:03:27,340 --> 00:03:28,380
- Okay. - Yes.

87
00:03:30,480 --> 00:03:35,590
(This contender is adding lots of green onions.)

88
00:03:33,250 --> 00:03:35,749
What's that? Is that cream cheese?

89
00:03:35,750 --> 00:03:37,150
- He looks so happy. - I know.

90
00:03:37,720 --> 00:03:38,760
He's in a good mood.

91
00:03:39,590 --> 00:03:41,629
He's the producer of "Life Experts," isn't he?

92
00:03:41,630 --> 00:03:42,690
- Yes. - I see.

93
00:03:44,490 --> 00:03:47,400
Hello. My shop is on Rodeo Street in Apgujeong.

94
00:03:47,860 --> 00:03:50,269
At the shop opened in 2020,

95
00:03:50,270 --> 00:03:53,369
I've been baking authentic Jewish bagels.

96
00:03:50,370 --> 00:03:52,970
(Traditional bagels using the skills obtained in New York)

97
00:03:53,370 --> 00:03:55,110
I'm Lee Sang Ho, the Life Expert.

98
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:55,269
(Life Expert, Lee Sang Ho)

99
00:03:55,270 --> 00:03:56,770
(Lots O Bagels in Apgujeong, former PD of "Life Experts")

100
00:03:56,640 --> 00:04:01,309
I've worked for SBS for 33 years.

101
00:03:57,170 --> 00:04:01,180
(Worked for SBS for 33 years as a producer)

102
00:04:01,310 --> 00:04:05,020
The last show I worked on was "Life Experts."

103
00:04:05,880 --> 00:04:08,749
After witnessing how dedicated they are,

104
00:04:08,750 --> 00:04:10,550
I thought I'd bake with true dedication too.

105
00:04:08,820 --> 00:04:10,420
(Let me bake bread with true dedication too.)

106
00:04:10,890 --> 00:04:14,220
I've introduced rice bagel that doesn't use flour at all.

107
00:04:14,690 --> 00:04:16,290
It's been very popular.

108
00:04:17,530 --> 00:04:20,099
I'm surprised to see that quite many contenders...

109
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:22,500
have changed their career to become bakers.

110
00:04:22,970 --> 00:04:25,399
Being a baker or pastry chef isn't easy.

111
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:26,800
But it's that intriguing.

112
00:04:30,410 --> 00:04:32,339
(Here's another contender who changed his career...)

113
00:04:32,340 --> 00:04:34,280
(after falling in love with baking.)

114
00:04:36,910 --> 00:04:38,380
(Glancing)

115
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:41,420
(Glancing again)

116
00:04:41,590 --> 00:04:43,490
(The reason he keeps grabbing attention)

117
00:04:50,860 --> 00:04:52,899
- I have a question. - Okay.

118
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:55,430
- Why is your nickname Baking Idol? - Right.

119
00:04:53,730 --> 00:04:56,600
(Baking Idol, Ju Young Seok)

120
00:04:56,630 --> 00:04:57,699
Baking Idol?

121
00:04:57,700 --> 00:04:59,640
- Is he an idol? - He might be a former idol.

122
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:01,669
I used to be an idol.

123
00:05:01,670 --> 00:05:02,869
Really? That's why.

124
00:05:02,870 --> 00:05:03,939
It was a long time ago.

125
00:05:03,940 --> 00:05:07,110
- That's why you're handsome. - No.

126
00:05:06,980 --> 00:05:09,209
(Baking Idol, Ju Young Seok)

127
00:05:09,210 --> 00:05:10,579
(Panpan in Paju, expanded to 15 stores)

128
00:05:09,350 --> 00:05:11,979
Did you know there's a former idol?

129
00:05:10,580 --> 00:05:11,950
(Former member of the idol group, Smash)

130
00:05:11,980 --> 00:05:13,120
Really?

131
00:05:13,620 --> 00:05:15,390
- Is it a guy? - Yes.

132
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:19,619
His nickname was Baking Idol, so I thought, "Idol?"

133
00:05:19,620 --> 00:05:22,460
And he really is a former idol. I didn't know that.

134
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:30,170
(Made a debut as a member of Smash in 2008)

135
00:05:26,260 --> 00:05:30,199
In 2008, I made my debut as a member of Smash,

136
00:05:30,200 --> 00:05:32,470
an idol group launched by Tony An's agency.

137
00:05:30,430 --> 00:05:34,570
(Young Seok was an idol for a while.)

138
00:05:35,170 --> 00:05:36,969
We weren't...

139
00:05:36,970 --> 00:05:38,580
We weren't that popular.

140
00:05:38,810 --> 00:05:41,510
So we got disbanded.

141
00:05:39,610 --> 00:05:42,550
(In the end, Smash got disbanded.)

142
00:05:42,580 --> 00:05:44,309
People in their 30s, which is how old I am,

143
00:05:44,310 --> 00:05:46,719
hold a fairly high social position.

144
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:50,889
But I felt like I was still living...

145
00:05:50,890 --> 00:05:52,790
at the bottom.

146
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:55,889
(While wondering what he could do,)

147
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:55,389
I often said, "What should I do?"

148
00:05:55,390 --> 00:05:58,459
My friend asked me, "Why don't you learn how to bake?"

149
00:05:55,890 --> 00:05:57,089
(his friend suggested,)

150
00:05:57,090 --> 00:05:59,200
("Why don't you learn how to bake?)

151
00:05:58,460 --> 00:06:00,960
I went to learn it even though I was afraid.

152
00:05:59,630 --> 00:06:02,630
(Baking was a new challenge for him.)

153
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:04,940
To be honest,

154
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:08,470
there's nothing I've put more effort into than baking.

155
00:06:08,810 --> 00:06:10,539
I put dough in the oven...

156
00:06:10,540 --> 00:06:13,479
and slept on a cardboard box for a short time.

157
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:15,880
I worked while sleeping only 2 to 3 hours a day.

158
00:06:16,210 --> 00:06:18,320
Still, I was happy.

159
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:23,650
I liked it. And I thought it was my last chance.

160
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:21,989
(Thinking it was his last chance,)

161
00:06:21,990 --> 00:06:24,760
(he put more efforts in baking.)

162
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:29,589
As a baker,

163
00:06:29,590 --> 00:06:32,530
I've opened a new chapter of my life.

164
00:06:32,830 --> 00:06:36,130
I believe I bake my dream every moment.

165
00:06:40,740 --> 00:06:42,870
He's moulding the croissant well.

166
00:06:43,170 --> 00:06:44,270
Is he good?

167
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:47,140
He rolled it well.

168
00:06:47,710 --> 00:06:48,710
It's his first compliment.

169
00:06:49,950 --> 00:06:52,980
(His moulding looks impeccable to the Masters.)

170
00:06:54,080 --> 00:06:57,720
The bread I'm going to make today is a milk cream croissant.

171
00:06:56,450 --> 00:06:58,860
(Milk cream croissant)

172
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:03,090
I mature the fresh cream.

173
00:07:02,590 --> 00:07:06,560
(Milk cream is made with matured fresh cream.)

174
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:08,400
I leave it for a few days before I use it.

175
00:07:11,170 --> 00:07:13,499
As the cream is flavourful, very light,

176
00:07:11,970 --> 00:07:15,340
(Matured fresh cream is light yet flavorful.)

177
00:07:13,500 --> 00:07:15,240
and fresh,

178
00:07:15,540 --> 00:07:18,709
I think it'll make the texture of croissant richer...

179
00:07:18,710 --> 00:07:22,080
because the bread is crispy.

180
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:26,349
I think Koreans like creams.

181
00:07:26,350 --> 00:07:28,080
- That's right. - Everyone's filling it with cream.

182
00:07:28,490 --> 00:07:29,919
Which cream do you like, Mimi?

183
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:32,720
Generally, I like milk cream.

184
00:07:31,860 --> 00:07:34,760
(Milk cream is Master Mimi's pick.)

185
00:07:33,820 --> 00:07:35,589
- Milk cream? - For the taste of the milk cream,

186
00:07:35,590 --> 00:07:38,090
(What are Master Mimi's standards as a cream bread expert?)

187
00:07:35,590 --> 00:07:36,789
I have my own standards.

188
00:07:36,790 --> 00:07:38,060
It can't be...

189
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:41,260
too heavy. It should be light.

190
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:41,399
(1. It should be light, not heavy.)

191
00:07:41,330 --> 00:07:43,469
And the taste of milk should be natural.

192
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:43,629
(2. The taste of milk should taste natural.)

193
00:07:43,470 --> 00:07:45,039
Also, it shouldn't be too sweet.

194
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:45,299
(3. It shouldn't be too sweet.)

195
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:49,370
The bread and cream have to match well in my mouth.

196
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:49,270
(4. The bread and cream have to match well.)

197
00:07:51,940 --> 00:07:53,280
I'm confident about my cream.

198
00:07:55,780 --> 00:07:58,950
I think Mimi will like it because it's fairly sweet.

199
00:07:55,880 --> 00:07:58,750
(Will it satisfy Master Mimi's palate?)

200
00:07:59,050 --> 00:08:00,879
- Hello. - Hello.

201
00:08:00,880 --> 00:08:04,150
Nice to meet you. I'm Ju Young Seok, the Baking Idol, from Paju.

202
00:08:03,150 --> 00:08:04,389
(Baking Idol, Ju Young Seok)

203
00:08:04,390 --> 00:08:06,120
(15 Panpan stores, including Paju, Former member of Smash)

204
00:08:04,490 --> 00:08:05,920
My signature bread...

205
00:08:06,460 --> 00:08:09,960
uses the cream I've developed over 8 or 9 years.

206
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:12,329
It's the pillar that allowed me to run my bakery...

207
00:08:12,330 --> 00:08:13,800
until now.

208
00:08:14,660 --> 00:08:18,170
We'll talk again while tasting the bread.

209
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:40,020
(He feels more nervous as he was confident about it.)

210
00:08:42,330 --> 00:08:45,130
(Only the crunchy sound of croissant fills up the space.)

211
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:09,420
(Thinking)

212
00:09:07,820 --> 00:09:10,850
Your dough-rolling technique...

213
00:09:11,420 --> 00:09:12,720
- is top-notch. - I agree.

214
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:14,690
- It's top-notch. - I agree.

215
00:09:15,490 --> 00:09:16,860
You have solid skills.

216
00:09:18,630 --> 00:09:21,870
The grain of the outer layer...

217
00:09:22,070 --> 00:09:23,300
was good, but...

218
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:32,040
Honestly, I like the cream even better.

219
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:34,140
- Yes. - Thank you.

220
00:09:35,910 --> 00:09:38,649
People of all ages and genders can go to your bakery.

221
00:09:38,650 --> 00:09:41,689
Both parents and children will find it tasty.

222
00:09:41,590 --> 00:09:44,350
(A flavor for all generations)

223
00:09:41,690 --> 00:09:44,390
It has a flavour one can share with others.

224
00:09:44,520 --> 00:09:47,519
It's something that'd be liked and enjoyed casually by everyone.

225
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:49,330
That's how light the cream tasted.

226
00:09:49,390 --> 00:09:51,129
I enjoyed it very much.

227
00:09:50,060 --> 00:09:52,730
(Master Mimi, an expert in cream bread, compliments it.)

228
00:09:51,130 --> 00:09:52,130
Thank you.

229
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:58,970
Will Ju Young Seok, the Baking Idol, get a pass?

230
00:09:57,470 --> 00:10:00,300
(Baking Idol Ju Young Seok's signature bread)

231
00:09:59,500 --> 00:10:01,840
Let's check the result.

232
00:10:01,570 --> 00:10:05,210
(Will milk cream croissant get a pass?)

233
00:10:07,280 --> 00:10:09,180
(Ju Young Seok, the Baking Idol, passed.)

234
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:11,580
- Thank you. - Contender Ju Young Seok,

235
00:10:12,820 --> 00:10:14,420
- Thank you. - Congratulations.

236
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:16,550
Well...

237
00:10:17,990 --> 00:10:21,760
It feels like those hard eight years or so are finally paying off.

238
00:10:22,130 --> 00:10:24,459
- It was really hard for me. - Goodness.

239
00:10:24,460 --> 00:10:26,199
- You're amazing. - Gosh.

240
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,460
- Good job. - Thank you.

241
00:10:31,530 --> 00:10:33,769
I almost cried...

242
00:10:33,770 --> 00:10:35,040
when I saw the look on the Masters' faces.

243
00:10:35,640 --> 00:10:38,479
I felt like Mimi gave me strength.

244
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:42,080
Master Lee had a warm smile on his face.

245
00:10:43,050 --> 00:10:44,550
His fatherly...

246
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,779
and warm smile...

247
00:10:46,780 --> 00:10:49,220
touched me very much.

248
00:10:50,850 --> 00:10:52,859
(Baking Idol, Ju Young Seok)

249
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:54,620
(The news of Young Seok's pass spreads.)

250
00:10:55,130 --> 00:10:57,430
Gosh. Everyone gets a pass.

251
00:10:57,660 --> 00:10:59,560
(A pass?)

252
00:11:00,430 --> 00:11:01,630
What are their standards?

253
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:03,130
- What are they? - The Masters' standards?

254
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:04,600
Do we need to be eloquent?

255
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:06,969
That's one thing, but more than anything,

256
00:11:06,970 --> 00:11:09,410
your bread needs to stand on its own merits.

257
00:11:12,680 --> 00:11:15,210
(A contender who has been listening quietly)

258
00:11:17,010 --> 00:11:19,180
