2096
01:26:40,400 --> 01:26:43,540
This bread has very little salt and no sugar at all.

2097
01:26:40,730 --> 01:26:43,470
(No salt, no sugar)

2098
01:26:43,770 --> 01:26:46,269
You can digest this bread well even if you eat it at 10pm.

2099
01:26:43,900 --> 01:26:47,470
(Bread that is digestible even when you eat it at 10pm.)

2100
01:26:46,270 --> 01:26:47,610
It's amazing.

2101
01:26:49,470 --> 01:26:53,610
(Bok Hee Bread)

2102
01:26:54,810 --> 01:26:57,150
(But...)

2103
01:26:57,320 --> 01:26:59,820
Your bread is supposed to have an open crust, but it doesn't.

2104
01:27:01,620 --> 01:27:02,620
No open crust.

2105
01:27:02,621 --> 01:27:04,920
Out of all the sourdough breads I had,

2106
01:27:05,360 --> 01:27:09,390
this is the most tangy and sour one.

2107
01:27:09,960 --> 01:27:12,530
I try not to make my bread sour as much as I can,

2108
01:27:13,200 --> 01:27:16,230
but it got too sour again. I regret that a little.

2109
01:27:16,840 --> 01:27:17,870
- No. - Gosh.

2110
01:27:17,870 --> 01:27:20,070
(Top Model Bakery Owner, Park Dool Sun fails.)

2111
01:27:17,970 --> 01:27:20,110
Contender Park Dool Sun has failed.

2112
01:27:21,410 --> 01:27:24,310
(Bok Hee Bread tasted the bitterness of failure.)

2113
01:27:21,410 --> 01:27:22,470
Thank you.

2114
01:27:22,640 --> 01:27:24,540
- Thank you for your hard work. - Thank you.

2115
01:27:25,610 --> 01:27:27,379
It's really difficult to make vegan bread.

2116
01:27:27,380 --> 01:27:29,479
Yes, I'm surprised so many people attempted it here.

2117
01:27:29,480 --> 01:27:30,520
- Yes. - Gosh.

2118
01:27:31,350 --> 01:27:32,480
What is that?

2119
01:27:33,420 --> 01:27:35,320
(Wild vegetables?)

2120
01:27:33,590 --> 01:27:35,449
- It looks like wild vegetables! - Right?

2121
01:27:35,450 --> 01:27:36,490
- And lotus root! - Lotus root.

2122
01:27:37,220 --> 01:27:39,119
He's using thistle and lotus root together?

2123
01:27:39,120 --> 01:27:41,360
Yes, lotus root and thistle.

2124
01:27:41,560 --> 01:27:42,730
Into the mixer.

2125
01:27:43,630 --> 01:27:45,930
(Grinding)

2126
01:27:49,130 --> 01:27:51,870
It's like he's making temple food.

2127
01:27:53,440 --> 01:27:55,110
Ground lotus root tastes so bad.

2128
01:27:57,180 --> 01:27:59,439
- I had nosebleeds a lot as a kid. - Yes.

2129
01:27:59,440 --> 01:28:01,709
And my grandmother used a home remedy for me...

2130
01:28:01,710 --> 01:28:02,749
- all the time, - Right.

2131
01:28:02,750 --> 01:28:05,219
- and gave me ground lotus roots. - Grandmothers do that.

2132
01:28:05,220 --> 01:28:07,820
And I remember I hated that when I was young.

2133
01:28:07,920 --> 01:28:10,160
(Even Master Narae was picky with her food.)

2134
01:28:09,050 --> 01:28:11,490
So I'm curious to see how that bread would taste.

2135
01:28:13,930 --> 01:28:15,830
It's bound to be healthy.

2136
01:28:17,200 --> 01:28:19,630
- I think it'll taste very mature. - I think so too.

2137
01:28:17,230 --> 01:28:19,700
(A mature taste)

2138
01:28:21,600 --> 01:28:24,740
(How would the lotus root thistle bread taste?)

2139
01:28:26,070 --> 01:28:27,710
(Yeoju Natural Man, Oh Seung Geun)

2140
01:28:28,940 --> 01:28:31,340
This is the bread with lotus root and thistle, right?

2141
01:28:32,080 --> 01:28:34,810
I can't wait to meet this Yeoju Natural Man.

2142
01:28:36,250 --> 01:28:37,280
Hello.

2143
01:28:47,690 --> 01:28:49,130
Thank you very much.

2144
01:28:48,160 --> 01:28:51,300
(Yeoju Natural Man shows off his shaven head.)

2145
01:28:49,260 --> 01:28:52,130
Could you introduce yourself and your signature bread?

2146
01:28:52,530 --> 01:28:55,829
I use temple food in Yeoju, Gyeonggi Province...

2147
01:28:55,830 --> 01:28:57,270
to make healthy breads.

2148
01:28:57,470 --> 01:28:59,470
I'm Yeoju Natural Man, Oh Seung Geun.

2149
01:28:57,670 --> 01:28:59,099
(Yeoju Natural Man, Oh Seung Geun)

2150
01:28:59,100 --> 01:29:00,440
(Ran a bakery in Yeoju-si for 8 years baking healthy bread)

2151
01:29:02,310 --> 01:29:04,110
I go around the nearby mountains...

2152
01:29:05,410 --> 01:29:08,009
and bake healthy breads...

2153
01:29:08,010 --> 01:29:09,919
with ingredients I find in nature.

2154
01:29:09,920 --> 01:29:11,680
That's where I got my nickname.

2155
01:29:13,450 --> 01:29:14,750
In the temple,

2156
01:29:14,250 --> 01:29:16,689
(He found healthy ingredients in nature at the temple.)

2157
01:29:15,120 --> 01:29:16,689
I found so many good ingredients.

2158
01:29:16,690 --> 01:29:19,590
They have scorched rice, rice, wild vegetables, and so on.

2159
01:29:16,690 --> 01:29:18,259
(Scorched rice, rice,)

2160
01:29:18,260 --> 01:29:20,190
(and wild vegetables)

2161
01:29:19,760 --> 01:29:21,960
And they all go so well with bread.

2162
01:29:22,130 --> 01:29:23,499
Every day, I pray...

2163
01:29:23,500 --> 01:29:26,160
and study ways to bake using different ingredients.

2164
01:29:26,900 --> 01:29:29,840
That's how I started baking bread with traditional Korean flavours,

2165
01:29:30,070 --> 01:29:32,970
and I chose one as my signature bread.

2166
01:29:33,870 --> 01:29:37,710
(Lotus root thistle bread)

2167
01:29:38,540 --> 01:29:41,380
Shall we dig in and share our thoughts?

2168
01:29:45,050 --> 01:29:46,590
I think I can smell the lotus root.

2169
01:29:47,390 --> 01:29:49,120
Should we dip the bread in perilla oil?

2170
01:29:49,150 --> 01:29:52,160
Yes, the dip has perilla oil and green plum preserves.

2171
01:29:52,760 --> 01:29:55,029
So the green plum preserves are underneath the oil?

2172
01:29:55,030 --> 01:29:57,200
Yes, it's at the bottom.

2173
01:29:55,430 --> 01:29:59,430
(Perilla oil, green plum preserves)

2174
01:30:01,500 --> 01:30:05,740
(He extracted the perilla oil during the contest.)

2175
01:30:09,440 --> 01:30:10,510
The perilla oil...

2176
01:30:12,880 --> 01:30:14,380
The thistle...

2177
01:30:13,680 --> 01:30:16,650
(The thistle...)

2178
01:30:19,220 --> 01:30:21,290
I've never been evaluated like this before.

2179
01:30:21,990 --> 01:30:24,860
I got very nervous when I got to it.

2180
01:30:25,960 --> 01:30:27,829
- It's usually very bitter. - Yes.

2181
01:30:27,830 --> 01:30:28,859
But with this bread...

2182
01:30:28,860 --> 01:30:30,960
How did you get rid of the bitterness of the thistle?

2183
01:30:31,560 --> 01:30:33,670
How did you get rid of the bitterness of the thistle?

2184
01:30:34,230 --> 01:30:36,100
Well, the bitterness...

2185
01:30:36,400 --> 01:30:39,969
is gone when you soak it in rice water for 12 hours.

2186
01:30:39,970 --> 01:30:41,669
- Twelve hours. - And use that same rice water...

2187
01:30:41,670 --> 01:30:43,040
to boil the thistle.

2188
01:30:43,140 --> 01:30:45,910
(Listening)

2189
01:30:43,740 --> 01:30:45,740
- That helps with the bitterness. - I see.

2190
01:30:47,480 --> 01:30:50,379
I had a lot of raw lotus roots as a child,

2191
01:30:50,380 --> 01:30:52,180
so I don't have good memories of it.

2192
01:30:55,050 --> 01:30:57,220
But even the decoration had a clean, rich flavour.

2193
01:30:57,720 --> 01:30:59,460
- The flavour wasn't uncomfortable, - That's right.

2194
01:30:59,660 --> 01:31:01,660
and they all mixed harmoniously.

2195
01:31:01,960 --> 01:31:04,960
Instead of using balsamic vinegar and olive oil,

2196
01:31:05,330 --> 01:31:07,099
I thought the idea of using traditional ingredients...

2197
01:31:07,100 --> 01:31:10,040
like perilla oil and lotus root for ciabatta was very creative.

2198
01:31:10,500 --> 01:31:14,410
Overall, the flavours went together very nicely.

2199
01:31:14,870 --> 01:31:19,180
(Yeoju Natural Man mostly received positive reviews.)

2200
01:31:15,140 --> 01:31:19,240
Let's see the results for Yeoju Natural Man.

2201
01:31:20,610 --> 01:31:24,120
(Would his results be positive as well?)

2202
01:31:25,350 --> 01:31:27,120
(Yeoju Natural Man, Oh Seung Geun passed.)

2203
01:31:27,990 --> 01:31:30,189
- Gosh. - Contender Oh Seung Geun passed.

2204
01:31:30,190 --> 01:31:31,259
- Thank you. - Yes.

2205
01:31:31,260 --> 01:31:32,459
- Thank you. - Great work.

2206
01:31:32,460 --> 01:31:34,229
In Korean fine dining,

2207
01:31:34,230 --> 01:31:36,660
