2208
01:31:36,900 --> 01:31:39,359
But if we were to use bread in Korean fine dining,

2209
01:31:39,360 --> 01:31:42,969
I think this type of bread would go very well.

2210
01:31:40,930 --> 01:31:44,340
(The taste would go well in Korean fine dining courses.)

2211
01:31:42,970 --> 01:31:44,500
It's very creative too.

2212
01:31:44,900 --> 01:31:48,369
This bread satisfied the thirst I've had for this matter,

2213
01:31:45,470 --> 01:31:49,010
(This bread satisfied Master Kwon Sung Jun's thirst.)

2214
01:31:48,370 --> 01:31:50,080
- so I'm very grateful. - Thank you so much.

2215
01:31:51,280 --> 01:31:54,450
I'll do my very best and try not to let you down.

2216
01:31:54,910 --> 01:31:56,010
- Thank you. - Goodbye.

2217
01:31:56,950 --> 01:31:58,919
- This bread is so good. - It really is.

2218
01:31:58,920 --> 01:32:00,789
- I can't believe it. - This is my favourite today.

2219
01:32:00,790 --> 01:32:01,790
Really?

2220
01:32:01,791 --> 01:32:03,320
- He's an honest man... - Right.

2221
01:32:03,150 --> 01:32:04,989
(Contender Oh Seung Geun's bread was charming...)

2222
01:32:03,490 --> 01:32:05,519
who went his own way in life without being greedy.

2223
01:32:04,990 --> 01:32:07,330
(because he went his own way and pursued it.)

2224
01:32:05,520 --> 01:32:07,860
- That's what craftsmanship is. - Yes.

2225
01:32:08,860 --> 01:32:11,800
(A strange noise fills the bread factory.)

2226
01:32:15,130 --> 01:32:16,570
Goodness, what is that?

2227
01:32:16,900 --> 01:32:18,070
What's that?

2228
01:32:22,270 --> 01:32:23,480
It's an air compressor.

2229
01:32:27,650 --> 01:32:29,610
It's used quite often for pastries.

2230
01:32:28,350 --> 01:32:30,019
(Air compressor)

2231
01:32:29,710 --> 01:32:31,979
When do you use it?

2232
01:32:30,020 --> 01:32:31,949
(Used in baking for coloring or creating details...)

2233
01:32:31,950 --> 01:32:33,690
(on chocolates or cake surfaces.)

2234
01:32:31,980 --> 01:32:33,490
- For molding chocolate and such. - You spray it like that.

2235
01:32:34,190 --> 01:32:35,220
I see. Like that?

2236
01:32:34,320 --> 01:32:36,419
(The contender shows off his elaborate skills.)

2237
01:32:36,420 --> 01:32:37,689
(Five-Star Pastry Chef, Cho Sang Min)

2238
01:32:37,260 --> 01:32:39,259
I've only worked at five-star hotels...

2239
01:32:37,690 --> 01:32:39,090
(Worked in a 5-star hotel, Sheraton Hotel, and Josun Palace Hotel)

2240
01:32:39,260 --> 01:32:42,130
from when I first started and even now.

2241
01:32:42,390 --> 01:32:46,430
That's how I got the nickname, Five-Star Pastry Chef.

2242
01:32:42,690 --> 01:32:43,960
(Picture provided by himself)

2243
01:32:47,100 --> 01:32:49,570
I'm the sous chef of the hotel I'm working at right now.

2244
01:32:47,830 --> 01:32:50,140
(Plays a pivotal role in the hotel as the sous chef)

2245
01:32:50,200 --> 01:32:52,569
Considering I'm 31 years old,

2246
01:32:52,570 --> 01:32:53,940
I became the sous chef rather quickly.

2247
01:32:54,970 --> 01:32:59,640
(The sous chef's elegant skills)

2248
01:33:03,950 --> 01:33:05,150
It really is beautiful.

2249
01:33:05,320 --> 01:33:07,520
- Like how they make it at hotels. - Right.

2250
01:33:07,950 --> 01:33:10,319
Using an air compressor requires a lot of technique.

2251
01:33:10,320 --> 01:33:12,259
Don't you have to spray it evenly?

2252
01:33:12,260 --> 01:33:13,689
Right, and you need to mind the temperature too.

2253
01:33:13,690 --> 01:33:16,959
Yes, you need to spray it well and consider the temperature.

2254
01:33:15,260 --> 01:33:16,960
(This technique requires delicacy.)

2255
01:33:16,960 --> 01:33:19,029
Back in the day, we didn't have such equipment,

2256
01:33:19,030 --> 01:33:20,099
so we rubbed it on with a toothbrush.

2257
01:33:20,100 --> 01:33:21,630
- Goodness. - You don't say.

2258
01:33:21,770 --> 01:33:22,799
Master Lee!

2259
01:33:21,900 --> 01:33:24,240
(The Masters don't know how to respond.)

2260
01:33:22,800 --> 01:33:24,440
That's so real.

2261
01:33:27,310 --> 01:33:29,170
(What is the sous chef's signature bread?)

2262
01:33:29,310 --> 01:33:30,610
Is that chocolate?

2263
01:33:31,140 --> 01:33:32,240
It's a chocolate sponge cake.

2264
01:33:32,640 --> 01:33:34,810
I think he's making the base of his dessert.

2265
01:33:35,680 --> 01:33:37,249
My signature bread...

2266
01:33:37,250 --> 01:33:39,880
