2276
01:33:56,070 --> 01:33:58,069
I also added raspberry to the cake...

2277
01:33:58,070 --> 01:34:01,640
to bring out the flavour of the chocolate.

2278
01:33:59,140 --> 01:34:02,110
(The raspberry makes the chocolate in the dessert taste richer.)

2279
01:34:02,310 --> 01:34:04,110
Is that like strawberry jam?

2280
01:34:04,310 --> 01:34:05,909
It's a compote.

2281
01:34:04,740 --> 01:34:05,909
(Compote)

2282
01:34:05,910 --> 01:34:07,650
(Jam made with fruits and sugar boiled together to keep the texture)

2283
01:34:05,910 --> 01:34:07,110
A raspberry compote.

2284
01:34:08,380 --> 01:34:10,319
That looks quite delicious.

2285
01:34:10,320 --> 01:34:12,749
- Why does he look so professional? - I know, right?

2286
01:34:12,750 --> 01:34:14,390
Everyone is so skilled.

2287
01:34:13,550 --> 01:34:15,190
(He seems very professional.)

2288
01:34:15,190 --> 01:34:17,089
The contender working with chocolate...

2289
01:34:17,090 --> 01:34:19,520
also seems to be doing a neat job.

2290
01:34:20,060 --> 01:34:22,090
She's also a sous chef.

2291
01:34:23,030 --> 01:34:25,729
(Parisienne Chef, Jung Min)

2292
01:34:23,260 --> 01:34:26,499
I'm Jung Min, and I work at Le Biscuit Alain Ducasse...

2293
01:34:25,730 --> 01:34:29,100
(The first Korean chef in Le Biscuit Alain Ducasse, Paris)

2294
01:34:26,500 --> 01:34:29,270
as the sous chef.

2295
01:34:29,930 --> 01:34:32,899
There are only two Alain Ducasse stores in the world,

2296
01:34:30,340 --> 01:34:33,710
(There are only two Alain Ducasse bakeries, in Paris and Japan.)

2297
01:34:32,900 --> 01:34:35,540
and I'm the only Korean working in them.

2298
01:34:35,970 --> 01:34:38,780
I've been working in Paris for nine years now.

2299
01:34:39,280 --> 01:34:41,650
Should we introduce Chef Alain Ducasse to everyone?

2300
01:34:39,610 --> 01:34:42,050
(Who is Chef Alain Ducasse?)

2301
01:34:42,050 --> 01:34:44,380
He's the chef with the most Michelin stars.

2302
01:34:42,880 --> 01:34:44,250
(The chef who has the most Michelin stars)

2303
01:34:44,450 --> 01:34:46,720
(The only person with 21 Michelin stars)

2304
01:34:45,120 --> 01:34:46,919
He truly is...

2305
01:34:46,920 --> 01:34:49,149
the GOAT of fine dining.

2306
01:34:47,050 --> 01:34:49,089
(The GOAT of fine dining)

2307
01:34:49,090 --> 01:34:50,290
(Gotsu?)

2308
01:34:49,150 --> 01:34:50,259
- Gotsu? - No.

2309
01:34:50,260 --> 01:34:51,459
- No, GOAT. - It means the best.

2310
01:34:51,460 --> 01:34:53,189
- Is it a Japanese chef? - Sorry?

2311
01:34:53,190 --> 01:34:54,860
- Is it a Japanese chef? - No...

2312
01:34:55,490 --> 01:34:58,530
(GOAT, English slang)

2313
01:34:55,660 --> 01:34:57,529
- It means "Greatest of All Time." - It's like...

2314
01:34:57,530 --> 01:34:58,629
It's slang.

2315
01:34:58,630 --> 01:35:01,070
- Like "awesome"? - Exactly.

2316
01:35:01,830 --> 01:35:02,970
I learn so much from you guys.

2317
01:35:04,040 --> 01:35:07,039
Chef Alain Ducasse believes...

2318
01:35:07,040 --> 01:35:09,970
that good desserts come from good ingredients.

2319
01:35:10,810 --> 01:35:12,009
That looks like chocolate.

2320
01:35:12,010 --> 01:35:13,410
- I think those are cacao nibs. - Cacao nibs.

2321
01:35:13,580 --> 01:35:15,409
These days, cacao beans are also classified...

2322
01:35:14,050 --> 01:35:18,580
(Cacao beans are classified in detail by origin.)

2323
01:35:15,410 --> 01:35:17,479
according to where they were grown,

2324
01:35:17,480 --> 01:35:18,780
just like coffee beans.

2325
01:35:18,920 --> 01:35:20,620
And each type has a different flavour.

2326
01:35:20,790 --> 01:35:22,889
I used three chocolates from different origins.

2327
01:35:22,620 --> 01:35:24,089
(Madagascar,)

2328
01:35:22,890 --> 01:35:25,159
These milk chocolates are from...

2329
01:35:24,090 --> 01:35:25,219
(Peru,)

2330
01:35:25,160 --> 01:35:27,660
Madagascar, Peru, and Togo.

2331
01:35:25,220 --> 01:35:27,730
(and Togo)

2332
01:35:27,890 --> 01:35:29,860
The name of this dessert is Tout choco.

2333
01:35:29,960 --> 01:35:31,359
It's French for...

2334
01:35:31,360 --> 01:35:35,430
a tart that has chocolate in every ingredient.

2335
01:35:35,770 --> 01:35:36,869
It's not too sweet,

2336
01:35:36,870 --> 01:35:39,299
and it helps you appreciate all the traits of chocolate.

2337
01:35:39,300 --> 01:35:42,340
That's why I chose this dessert as my signature bread.

2338
01:35:43,710 --> 01:35:46,910
(Parisienne Chef's dessert is filled with chocolate.)

2339
01:35:49,650 --> 01:35:51,750
Since this is a tart,

2340
01:35:51,880 --> 01:35:54,090
I focused a lot on the foncage, or the tart shell.

2341
01:35:54,550 --> 01:35:57,559
And a good dessert should be appreciated with your eyes too.

2342
01:35:57,560 --> 01:36:01,130
So I put a lot of work into decorating the tart as well.

2343
01:36:05,760 --> 01:36:08,800
(She finishes with a chocolate garnish on top.)

2344
01:36:08,770 --> 01:36:10,439
I think there'll be many new things for me in that tart.

2345
01:36:10,440 --> 01:36:12,200
- It looks really promising. - It really does.

2346
01:36:12,670 --> 01:36:14,410
(Meanwhile,)

2347
01:36:15,470 --> 01:36:17,480
He's done spraying and molding the chocolate now.

2348
01:36:15,570 --> 01:36:19,380
(Contender Cho Sang Min is molding chocolate.)

2349
01:36:20,980 --> 01:36:23,580
(He's making chocolate decorations to put on his cake.)

2350
01:36:26,780 --> 01:36:28,850
(But then he starts to run.)

2351
01:36:28,490 --> 01:36:29,920
Goodness, he shouldn't leave right now.

2352
01:36:30,420 --> 01:36:32,390
- Why not? - The chocolate will get too thick.

2353
01:36:33,090 --> 01:36:35,030
The timing of getting it out of the mold is important too.

2354
01:36:35,130 --> 01:36:37,829
Take it out too soon, and it'll be too thin and break.

2355
01:36:37,830 --> 01:36:40,799
Take it out too late, and the shell will become too thick.

2356
01:36:40,800 --> 01:36:43,130
The timing and temperature must all be considered.

2357
01:36:44,070 --> 01:36:47,410
(Contender Cho Sang Min returned to his station a little late.)

2358
01:36:48,640 --> 01:36:51,580
At the beginning of the contest,

2359
01:36:51,880 --> 01:36:54,710
I didn't think I would have any problems.

2360
01:36:55,280 --> 01:36:56,310
However,

2361
01:36:57,220 --> 01:36:58,720
there was a problem.

2362
01:36:59,720 --> 01:37:02,550
(What problem is he facing?)

2363
01:37:02,620 --> 01:37:04,060
I think this is too thick.

2364
01:37:04,290 --> 01:37:06,360
(The chocolate was molded too thickly.)

2365
01:37:07,190 --> 01:37:09,190
I molded the chocolate...

2366
01:37:09,390 --> 01:37:10,630
and was going to take it out, but...

2367
01:37:13,970 --> 01:37:17,540
(The chocolate is stuck in the mold.)

2368
01:37:17,500 --> 01:37:19,400
Please...

2369
01:37:19,540 --> 01:37:20,540
Come out.

2370
01:37:24,510 --> 01:37:26,210
They either didn't come out or came out broken.

2371
01:37:28,910 --> 01:37:33,480
(His decoration is split into two.)

2372
01:37:34,890 --> 01:37:37,720
(He tries again with another mold.)

2373
01:37:40,330 --> 01:37:41,930
Goodness.

2374
01:37:43,660 --> 01:37:45,659
He hit it too hard, and it broke.

2375
01:37:45,660 --> 01:37:47,170
- Just now? - Yes.

2376
01:37:47,730 --> 01:37:49,970
I think he's trying to piece it back together now.

2377
01:37:51,540 --> 01:37:53,610
(He tries to stick them together using melted chocolate.)

2378
01:37:54,840 --> 01:37:55,840
He's sticking them.

2379
01:37:55,840 --> 01:37:56,840
He's giving first aid.

2380
01:37:57,610 --> 01:38:00,480
(Would he be able to fix his chocolate decorations?)

2381
01:38:00,410 --> 01:38:01,650
Gosh.

2382
01:38:02,180 --> 01:38:04,450
- No. - It really is too thick.

2383
01:38:05,850 --> 01:38:08,490
(He has 1 hour and 19 minutes left.)

2384
01:38:05,950 --> 01:38:07,190
I have an hour and 19 minutes left.

2385
01:38:09,250 --> 01:38:10,759
(Parisienne Chef, Jung Min)

2386
01:38:10,760 --> 01:38:13,260
(Contender Jung Min goes out to meet the Masters.)

2387
01:38:13,630 --> 01:38:15,660
I'm really excited for the evaluation.

2388
01:38:16,160 --> 01:38:20,269
Looking at it from the French perspective,

2389
01:38:20,270 --> 01:38:22,100
I'm confident with my dessert.

2390
01:38:24,600 --> 01:38:26,200
Would the next contender please enter the room?

2391
01:38:28,870 --> 01:38:30,140
- Good luck! - Yes!

2392
01:38:32,080 --> 01:38:33,080
- Hello. - Hello!

2393
01:38:33,081 --> 01:38:35,350
- Hello! - Nice to meet you.

2394
01:38:36,880 --> 01:38:40,120
My signature bread is called Tout choco.

2395
01:38:39,220 --> 01:38:41,820
(Tout choco)

2396
01:38:40,220 --> 01:38:41,989
It's French for "everything chocolate."

2397
01:38:41,990 --> 01:38:44,359
Everything is made out of chocolate.

2398
01:38:42,190 --> 01:38:43,589
(Tout choco)

2399
01:38:43,590 --> 01:38:45,560
(French for "everything chocolate")

2400
01:38:44,360 --> 01:38:47,429
At the very bottom, the chocolate pate sucree...

2401
01:38:47,430 --> 01:38:50,960
with cacao powder gives a bittersweet flavour.

2402
01:38:50,860 --> 01:38:52,359
(Cacao nibs garnish)

2403
01:38:51,200 --> 01:38:53,029
This is a tart...

2404
01:38:52,360 --> 01:38:54,069
(Chocolate cream ganache montee)

2405
01:38:53,030 --> 01:38:55,899
that highlights the many qualities of chocolate...

2406
01:38:54,070 --> 01:38:55,670
(Bittersweet foncage tart shell)

2407
01:38:55,900 --> 01:38:57,270
with its bittersweet taste.

2408
01:38:56,270 --> 01:38:57,270
(Will her bittersweet foncage tart shell...)

2409
01:38:57,271 --> 01:38:59,640
(charm the Korean Masters as well?)

2410
01:38:57,900 --> 01:39:00,240
Then should we all take a bite?

2411
01:39:18,860 --> 01:39:22,230
I really love chocolate.

2412
01:39:22,830 --> 01:39:25,060
- I see. - And out of...

2413
01:39:26,400 --> 01:39:28,869
this is by far my favourite one.

2414
01:39:28,870 --> 01:39:29,929
Thank you so much.

2415
01:39:29,930 --> 01:39:31,499
It was so delicious,

2416
01:39:31,500 --> 01:39:33,939
and I don't think I can make any other comments about it.

2417
01:39:33,940 --> 01:39:35,370
Thank you for this dessert.

2418
01:39:35,910 --> 01:39:37,880
That compliment alone was more than enough for me.

2419
01:39:40,550 --> 01:39:44,320
(Tout choco moved Master Mimi with its rich flavor. Will it pass?)

2420
01:39:47,420 --> 01:39:51,320
The filling is quite watery.

2421
01:39:51,520 --> 01:39:54,390
(The filling is flowing out.)

2422
01:39:51,560 --> 01:39:54,459
Did you intend it to have this texture?

2423
01:39:54,460 --> 01:39:55,860
Or did you run out of time to thicken it?

2424
01:39:56,560 --> 01:39:59,060
Yes, I didn't have too much time,

2425
01:40:00,470 --> 01:40:03,800
and I had to rush through things.

2426
01:40:04,040 --> 01:40:05,470
I can see that.

2427
01:40:07,410 --> 01:40:11,210
(An unexpected comment)

2428
01:40:08,710 --> 01:40:13,210
Let's see the result for Contender Jung Min.

2429
01:40:15,580 --> 01:40:18,380
(What will happen to the sous chef of Alain Ducasse?)

2430
01:40:19,050 --> 01:40:21,590
(Will she pass or fail?)

2431
01:40:26,460 --> 01:40:32,260
(Parisienne Chef, Jung Min passed.)

2432
01:40:33,100 --> 01:40:35,970
(While everyone is celebrating...)

2433
01:40:38,470 --> 01:40:40,270
(Sighing)

2434
01:40:40,270 --> 01:40:42,470
I felt pressed for time,

2435
01:40:42,510 --> 01:40:44,239
and after having one mental breakdown,

2436
01:40:44,240 --> 01:40:45,980
it was hard for me to relax.

2437
01:40:46,240 --> 01:40:48,050
- Thank you. - Congratulations.

2438
01:40:47,210 --> 01:40:50,720
(Contender Jung Min passed,)

2439
01:40:48,280 --> 01:40:49,380
- Thank you. - Yes.

2440
01:40:52,980 --> 01:40:56,620
(but Contender Cho Sang Min is still wrestling with chocolate.)

2441
01:41:01,390 --> 01:41:03,800
I usually have no trouble with this.

2442
01:41:04,360 --> 01:41:07,800
And I blamed myself for not getting this right in a contest.

2443
01:41:08,300 --> 01:41:10,970
(He eventually gives up on putting the pieces back together.)

2444
01:41:16,940 --> 01:41:19,009
But at that point, I still thought I could do it again,

2445
01:41:19,010 --> 01:41:20,140
since I had some time left.

2446
01:41:20,810 --> 01:41:23,250
(He molds chocolate for the second time.)

2447
01:41:23,750 --> 01:41:24,820
Please...

2448
01:41:25,550 --> 01:41:26,820
(The chocolate is stuck.)

2449
01:41:28,390 --> 01:41:29,790
My gosh.

2450
01:41:35,790 --> 01:41:37,860
It's not coming out.

2451
01:41:44,200 --> 01:41:46,200
(Contender Cho Sang Min's station is completely ruined.)

2452
01:41:51,140 --> 01:41:53,410
Producer?

2453
01:41:54,180 --> 01:41:55,210
I can give up, right?

2454
01:41:56,950 --> 01:42:01,090
(What would happen to Contender Cho Sang Min?)

2455
01:42:01,250 --> 01:42:03,220
This is what we all wanted to see.

2456
01:42:01,750 --> 01:42:03,320
(What we all wanted to see...)

2457
01:42:03,690 --> 01:42:06,390
(are bakers who bake for life compete with each other.)

2458
01:42:03,690 --> 01:42:05,689
Bakers who bake for life.

2459
01:42:05,690 --> 01:42:10,260
- As part of the national team... - I feel energy in this bread.

2460
01:42:07,390 --> 01:42:10,290
(The professionals show off their prowess,)

2461
01:42:11,300 --> 01:42:12,399
This is like the final round.

2462
01:42:12,400 --> 01:42:16,270
- That's the middle school student? - I'm going to win, anyway.

2463
01:42:12,430 --> 01:42:19,440
(but the rookies can overthrow them as well.)

2464
01:42:17,200 --> 01:42:19,239
- I'm so excited. - He's like a professional.

2465
01:42:19,240 --> 01:42:22,240
Thirty-one contenders, you all have proven yourselves.

2466
01:42:19,800 --> 01:42:22,170
(Out of 31 contenders, who will be the one to win the war?)

2467
01:42:22,440 --> 01:42:24,939
Round 2 will be a team mission.

2468
01:42:22,840 --> 01:42:25,310
(The mission for Round 2 is overwhelming.)

2469
01:42:24,940 --> 01:42:26,739
- Round 2 will be a team mission. - Gosh.

2470
01:42:26,740 --> 01:42:27,950
A team mission already?

2471
01:42:27,980 --> 01:42:29,449
This isn't going to be easy.

2472
01:42:29,450 --> 01:42:32,049
I had no idea we'd do a team mission so soon.

2473
01:42:32,050 --> 01:42:33,380
I want to win no matter what.

2474
01:42:33,750 --> 01:42:34,849
How is this possible?

2475
01:42:34,850 --> 01:42:36,890
Then there's only one thing we can do.

2476
01:42:36,990 --> 01:42:38,720
(Only the 1st place can survive.)

2477
01:42:37,090 --> 01:42:38,720
We win first place.

2478
01:42:39,320 --> 01:42:41,560
Our team is not very confident...

2479
01:42:42,690 --> 01:42:43,690
of losing.

2480
01:42:42,690 --> 01:42:43,690
(I'm confident that I won't lose.)

2481
01:42:44,760 --> 01:42:45,860
This has to be first place.

2482
01:42:47,800 --> 01:42:49,869
- This is amazing. - I'm so excited.

2483
01:42:47,900 --> 01:42:49,930
(The contenders fight head-to-head.)

2484
01:42:49,870 --> 01:42:51,740
- There are so many twists. - What is that?

2485
01:42:52,840 --> 01:42:56,710
- There is an additional passer. - Really?

2486
01:42:52,870 --> 01:42:56,710
(The additional passer who can change the game)

2487
01:42:56,940 --> 01:42:58,440
I will announce the additional passer now.

2488
01:42:58,710 --> 01:42:59,840
Who will it be?

2489
01:43:00,610 --> 01:43:03,980
(Who is the additional contender that passed?)

2490
01:43:00,680 --> 01:43:03,750
I want to win first place. I even came back from the dead.
